{"id": 225036602, "title": "DP World is a Tier 1 Partner of the International Cricket Council", "text": "DP World Group (DP World), the leading global provider of logistics services and integrated smart supply chain solutions, today announced the expansion of its partnership with the International Cricket Council, the governing body for cricket worldwide, in conjunction with global anticipation for the holding of the Men\u2019s T20 World Cup, During which the Council will organize 55 matches across nine host sites in the United States of America and the West Indies from June 1 to 29. 16 group stage matches will be held in New York, Texas and Florida, marking the first time the United States of America has witnessed the holding of this tournament. Since June 2023, the DP World Group has collaborated closely with the International Cricket Council, to help deliver cricket equipment at the grassroots level and provide smart logistics services during the most important ICC events. DP World is now moving to the first-tier partner category within the International Cricket Council\u2019s portfolio of partners, confirming the commitment of its leading global brand to its mission to develop the sport throughout the world in the long term. DP World contributed to the World Series of Cricket by providing customized solutions to transport 10 grass pitches grown in Florida over 1,200 miles to the Nassau County International Cricket Stadium in New York and the nearby training site; A fleet of more than 20 vehicles transported the match and training pitches north on a two-day trip, with each pitch carefully prepared for transport and wrapped to preserve it during the journey to New York. DP World\u2019s advanced logistics capabilities ensured the transport of the Nassau County International Stadium pitches. For cricket in the best possible conditions.", "summary": "<p>DP World Group (DP World), the leading global provider of logistics services and integrated smart supply chain solu